'''Gustavo Rubén Caballero González''' (born 21 September 2001) is a Paraguayan professional [[footballer]] who plays for {{English football updater|Portsmou}} club [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]], on loan from [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] club [[Santos FC|Santos]], and the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]]. Mainly a [[Midfielder#Winger|winger]], he can also play as a [[Forward (association football)|forward]].

He began his career in his country's [[APF División de Honor]], playing 116 games and scoring 19 goals for [[Club Deportivo Capiatá|Deportivo Capiatá]], [[Sportivo Ameliano]], and [[Nacional Asunción]]. After finishing as joint top scorer of the [[Apertura and Clausura|Apertura]] in [[2025 Copa de Primera|2025]], he transferred to Santos, who then loaned him to Portsmouth.

Caballero represented the [[Paraguay national under-23 football team|Paraguay under-23 team]] at the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Olympic tournament]]. He made his senior international debut in 2026.

==Club career==
===Deportivo Capiatá===
A [[Deportivo Capiatá]] youth graduate, Caballero signed his first professional contract on 1 July 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/DCapiataOficial2008/posts/el-contrato-que-todo-jugador-desea-firmar-es-la-que-suscribieron-hoy-los-juvenil/2419748488064418/|title=El contrato que todo jugador desea firmar es la que suscribieron hoy los juveniles Gustavo Caballero y Fernando Bracho convirtiéndose así en jugadores del Deportivo Capiatá por 4 años y son integrantes del plantel principal!|trans-title=The contract which every player wants to sign is the one which the youngsters Gustavo Caballero and Fernando brach signed today becoming players of Deportivo Capiatá for 4 years and are members of the first team!|publisher=[[Facebook]]|work=Deportivo Capiatá|language=es|date=1 July 2019|accessdate=21 July 2025}}</ref> He made his debut in the [[Paraguayan Primera División]] on 12 July, starting for in a 1–0 home win over [[Sportivo Luqueño]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Con gol de Sasá, Capiatá castigó a Luqueño|trans-title=With goal from Sasá, Capiatá punished Luqueño |url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2019/07/12/con-gol-de-sasa-capiata-castigo-a-luqueno/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=Versus |date=12 July 2019 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

Caballero featured in seven league matches for Capiatá during the [[2019 Paraguayan Primera División season|2019 season]], as the club suffered relegation, and also helped the side to reach the semifinals of the [[2019 Copa Paraguay]].

===Sportivo Ameliano===
After the 2020 season was cancelled due to the [[COVID-19 pandemic in Paraguay|COVID-19 pandemic]], Caballero also spent the 2021 campaign unemployed before going on a trial at [[Sportivo Ameliano]] in January 2022; initially a member of the reserve team, he impressed during the pre-season and earned himself a first team spot.<ref>{{Cite tweet |author=Versus |user=SomosVersusPY |number=1505927039307722760 |date=21 March 2022 |title="Gustavo Caballero vino a prueba a la reserva, lo llevamos a la pretemporada y ayer hizo un gran partido" Humberto García, Técnico de #Ameliano en #VersusRadio @Universo970py @SomosGENAhora |trans-title="Gustavo Caballero came on a trial for the reserves, we took him to pre-season and he played a great match yesterday" Humberto García, manager of #Ameliano at #VersusRadio @Universo970py @SomosGENAhora |language=es |access-date=21 July 2025}}</ref> He scored his first professional goal on 20 March 2022, netting the opener in a 2–0 away win over [[Club Olimpia|Olimpia]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2022/10/05/gustavo-caballero-figura-de-nacional-confeso-su-fanatismo-por-olimpia/|title=Gustavo Caballero, figura de Nacional, confesó su fanatismo por Olimpia|trans-title=Gustavo Caballero, Nacional's key man, confessed his fanaticism for Olimpia|publisher=Versus|language=es|date=5 October 2022|accessdate=21 July 2025}}</ref>

Caballero contributed with two goals and two assists in 12 matches for Ameliano during the [[2022 Paraguayan Primera División season#Torneo Apertura|2022 Apertura tournament]].

===Nacional Asunción===
In July 2022, Caballero joined [[Club Nacional|Nacional Asunción]], who had been in irregular form and mid-table positions in the first half of the season.<ref name=versus>{{cite news |title=Gustavo Caballero, el futbolista que sorprendió en Ameliano y ahora refuerza Nacional|trans-title=Gustavo Caballero, the footballer who surprised at Ameliano and now bolsters Nacional|url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2022/07/13/gustavo-caballero-el-futbolista-que-sorprendio-en-ameliano-y-ahora-refuerza-nacional/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=Versus |date=13 July 2022 |language=Spanish}}</ref> In his second match for ''La Academia'' on 25 July, he scored his first goal in a 2–1 win at [[12 de Octubre Football Club|12 de Octubre]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Nacional se convierte en escolta y hunde al 12 de Octubre|trans-title=Nacional go defensive and sink 12 de Octubre |url=https://d10.ultimahora.com/nacional-se-convierte-escolta-y-hunde-al-12-octubre-n3014308 |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=D10 |date=25 July 2022 |language=Spanish}}</ref>

On 28 February 2023, Caballero scored his first continental goal in the [[Copa Libertadores]], albeit in a 5–1 loss away to [[Sporting Cristal]] of Peru, eliminating his side 5–3 on aggregate; he was soon afterwards demoted to the [[reserve team]] as a punishment for alleged tactical disobedience.<ref>{{cite news |title=Gustavo Caballero, separado del equipo: "Supuestamente soy desobediente tácticamente"|trans-title=Gustavo Caballero, separated from the team: "Apparently I am tactically disobedient"|url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2023/03/21/gustavo-caballero-separado-del-equipo-supuestamente-soy-desobediente-tacticamente/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=Versus |date=21 March 2023 |language=Spanish}}</ref> 

====Loan to Ameliano====
In July 2023, Caballero returned to Ameliano for the second half of [[2023 Paraguayan Primera División season|the season]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Altas y bajas de los 12 clubes de cara al torneo Clausura 2023|trans-title=Ins and outs of the 12 clubs ahead of the 2023 Clausura tournament |url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2023/07/06/altas-y-bajas-de-los-12-clubes-de-cara-al-torneo-clausura-2023/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=Versus |date=6 July 2023 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He only managed to make eight appearances for the side, with only three starts.

====Breakthrough====
Back to Nacional for the [[2024 Paraguayan Primera División season|2024 campaign]], Caballero soon established himself as a starter. On 5 September of that year, he scored a [[hat-trick]] in a 5–0 [[Copa Paraguay]] away routing of [[Club Cristóbal Colón de Juan Augusto Saldívar|Cristóbal Colón de Juan Augusto Saldívar]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.radionacional.gov.py/2024/09/05/nacional-golea-al-cristobal-colon-y-clasifica-a-los-octavos-de-final-de-la-copa-paraguay/|title=Nacional golea al Cristóbal Colón y clasifica a los octavos de final de la Copa Paraguay|trans-title=Nacional thrash Cristóbal Colón and qualify to the round of 16 of the Copa Paraguay|publisher=[[Radio Nacional del Paraguay]]|language=es|date=5 September 2024|accessdate=21 July 2025}}</ref> His performances attracted the interest of Olimpia,<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.versus.com.py/hoy/2024/12/11/olimpia-tambien-mira-por-barrio-obrero/|title=Olimpia también mira por barrio Obrero|trans-title=Olimpia also look to the Obrero neighborhood|publisher=Versus|language=es|date=11 December 2024|accessdate=21 July 2025}}</ref> but nothing came of it.

Caballero was the top scorer of the [[2025 Paraguayan Primera División season#Torneo Apertura|2025 Apertura tournament]] with nine goals (along with [[Juan Iturbe]]), which led to a move to [[Club Libertad|Libertad]] on 7 July of that year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/2025/07/07/libertad-caballero-fuerte-apuesta-del-campeon/|title=Libertad: Caballero, fuerte apuesta del campeón|trans-title=Libertad: Caballero, high bet from the champions|publisher=[[ABC Color]]|language=es|date=7 July 2025|accessdate=21 July 2025}}</ref> Five days later, however, the deal collapsed amidst interest from foreign clubs.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.versus.com.py/hoy/2025/07/12/cambio-de-planes-gustavo-caballero-finalmente-no-sera-jugador-de-libertad/|title=Cambio de planes: Gustavo Caballero finalmente no será jugador de Libertad|trans-title=Change of plans: Gustavo Caballero will not be a Libertad player|publisher=Versus|language=es|date=12 July 2025|accessdate=21 July 2025}}</ref>

===Santos===
In July 2025, [[Campeonato Brasileiro Série A]] side [[CR Vasco da Gama|Vasco da Gama]] made an offer to obtain Caballero on loan for [[United States dollar|US$]]400,000 with an option to purchase for US$2.2 million.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Cardoso |first1=Leandro |title=Vasco oficializa proposta por atacante internacional|trans-title=Vasco confirm offer for international attacker|url=https://www.terra.com.br/esportes/vasco/vasco-oficializa-proposta-por-atacante-internacional,b7b377fd1359c4df19861d594e064976rnh5fvhu.html |access-date=16 August 2025 |publisher=[[Terra (company)|Terra]] |date=17 July 2025 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> On 24 July however, [[Santos FC|Santos]] of the same league announced his signing on a four-year contract, paying US$1.6 million for 50% of his economic rights.<ref>{{cite news |title=Santos anuncia a contratação do atacante paraguaio Gustavo Caballero|trans-title=Santos announce the signing of Paraguayan attacker Gustavo Caballero|url=https://ge.globo.com/sp/santos-e-regiao/futebol/times/santos/noticia/2025/07/24/santos-anuncia-a-contratacao-do-atacante-paraguaio-gustavo-caballero.ghtml |access-date=16 August 2025 |publisher=ge |date=24 July 2025 |language=Portuguese}}</ref> 

Caballero made his debut for ''Peixe'' on 26 July 2025, being deployed as a [[right wing-back]] in a 2–2 away draw against [[Sport Club do Recife|Sport Recife]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.versus.com.py/hoy/2025/07/27/gustavo-caballero-tuvo-un-accidentado-debut-en-el-santos/|title=Gustavo Caballero tuvo un accidentado debut en el Santos|trans-title=Gustavo Caballero had a troubled debut at Santos|publisher=Versus|language=es|date=27 July 2025|accessdate=27 July 2025}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the club on 10 August, netting the winner in a 2–1 away success over [[Cruzeiro EC|Cruzeiro]]; he also provided the assist to [[Guilherme (footballer, born 1995)|Guilherme]]'s equaliser.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uol.com.br/esporte/futebol/ultimas-noticias/gazeta-esportiva/2025/08/11/decisivo-caballero-celebra-vitoria-do-santos-mostrou-a-nossa-capacidade.htm|title=Decisivo, Caballero exalta vitória do Santos: 'Mostrou nossa capacidade'|trans-title=Decisive, Caballero praises Santos' win: 'Showed our capacity'|publisher=[[Universo Online|UOL Esporte]]|language=pt-BR|date=11 August 2025|accessdate=11 August 2025}}</ref>

====Loan to Portsmouth====
On 2 February 2026, the last day of the [[transfer window]], Caballero was loaned to [[EFL Championship]] club [[Portsmouth F.C.|Portsmouth]] for the rest of the [[2025–26 EFL Championship|season]]. Manager [[John Mousinho]] said that he had been tracking him since the previous year.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Lacey |first1=Pepe |title=Portsmouth transfer deadline-day business continues as South American star seals switch |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/portsmouth-fc/portsmouthfc-news-gustavocaballero-transfer-santos-deadlineday-loan-5498256 |access-date=2 February 2026 |work=[[The News (Portsmouth)]] |date=2 February 2026}}</ref>

Caballero made his debut for Pompey on 7 February, replacing [[Andre Dozzell]] for the last 11 minutes of a 1–0 loss at [[Preston North End F.C.|Preston North End]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=McMahon |first1=Mark |title=Why Portsmouth will have seen Gustavo Caballero as a 'risk' worth taking - the view from Paraguay |url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/portsmouth-fc/portsmouth-fc-santos-gustavo-caballero-paraguay-risk-worth-taking-5510258 |access-date=2 April 2026 |work=[[The News (Portsmouth)]] |date=10 February 2026}}</ref> Two weeks later, he scored his first goal for the club in a 3–1 victory over [[Millwall F.C.|Millwall]] at [[The Den]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Millwall 1&ndash;3 Portsmouth |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c2k8gvq0n49t |access-date=2 April 2026 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=21 February 2026}}</ref>

==International career==
===Under-23 team===
Caballero made his debut for the [[Paraguay national under-23 football team|Paraguay national under-23 team]] on 8 June 2024, as a [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] in a 4–0 [[friendly match|friendly]] loss to neighbours [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]]. He was named in the squad for the [[Football at the 2024 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2024 Olympic event]] in France, but was moved to standby after veteran [[Fabián Balbuena]] received late permission from [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Roberto Jr. Fernández y Fabián Balbuena, citados a París 2024|trans-title=Roberto Jr. Fernández and Fabián Balbuena, called up to Paris 2024 |url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/seleccion-paraguaya/2024/07/08/roberto-jr-fernandez-y-fabian-balbuena-convocados-a-los-juegos-olimpicos/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=[[ABC Color]] |date=8 July 2024}}</ref>

Caballero was restored to the team days later when [[Fabrizio Peralta]] was denied permission by his Brazilian club [[Cruzeiro Esporte Clube|Cruzeiro]],<ref>{{cite news |title=Gustavo Caballero, sustituto de Fabrizio Peralta en París 2024|trans-title=Gustavo Caballero, Fabrizio Peralta's replacement at Paris 2024 |url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/seleccion-paraguaya/2024/07/10/gustavo-caballero-el-sustituto-de-fabrizio-peralta-en-paris-2024/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=[[ABC Color]] |date=10 July 2024 |language=Spanish}}</ref> and then dropped again as [[Julio Enciso (footballer, born 2004)|Julio Enciso]] was allowed to play by [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Refuerzo estrella: Julio Enciso está para jugar los Juegos Olímpicos|trans-title=Star addition: Julio Enciso will play in the Olympic Games|url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2024/07/13/refuerzo-estrella-julio-enciso-esta-para-jugar-los-juegos-olimpicos/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=Versus |date=13 July 2024 |language=Spanish}}</ref> On the day before the tournament, he was finally reinstalled in the squad when [[Diego González (footballer, born 2003)|Diego González]] suffered an injury.<ref>{{cite news |title=El sentido mensaje de Diego González tras quedar fuera: "Tenía muchas ganas"|trans-title=Diego González's heartfelt message after being cut: "I was looking forward so much"|url=https://www.versus.com.py/versus/2024/07/23/el-sentido-mensaje-de-diego-gonzalez-tras-quedar-fuera-tenia-muchas-ganas/ |access-date=27 July 2024 |publisher=Versus |date=23 July 2024 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He played in all three matches in the group stage, but was an unused substitute in Paraguay's quarterfinal loss to [[Egypt national under-23 football team|Egypt]].

===Senior team===
In March 2026, Caballero was called up to the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]] for friendly matches away to [[Greece national football team|Greece]] and against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]] in France.<ref>{{cite news |title=Diego Gómez y Gustavo Caballero, los primeros en suelo griego|trans-title=Diego Gómez and Gustavo Caballero, the first on Greek soil|url=https://www.abc.com.py/deportes/futbol/seleccion-paraguaya/2026/03/22/diego-gomez-y-gustavo-caballero-los-primeros-en-suelo-griego/ |access-date=2 April 2026 |work=[[ABC Color]] |date=22 March 2026 |language=Spanish}}</ref> He made his debut on 27 March in a 1–0 win over Greece as a substitute for the last 22 minutes,<ref>{{cite news |title=Paraguay venció a Grecia en uno de los amistosos internacional de cara al Mundial 2026|trans-title=Paraguay defeated Greece in one of the international friendlies ahead of the 2026 World Cup|url=https://www.tycsports.com/amistosos-de-selecciones/amistosos-internacionales-masc-2026-grecia-vs-paraguay-amistosos-id720675.html |access-date=2 April 2026 |publisher=[[TyC Sports]] |date=27 March 2026 |language=Spanish}}</ref> and four days later at the [[Stade Bollaert-Delelis]] in [[Lens, Pas-de-Calais|Lens]], he came off the bench to score a consolation goal in a 2–1 loss to Morocco.<ref>{{cite news |title=Portsmouth's Caballero on target in Paraguay loss |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/cdxkvw5wv61o |access-date=2 April 2026 |publisher=[[BBC Sport]] |date=1 April 2026}}</ref>

On 1 June 2026, Caballero was included in [[Gustavo Alfaro]]'s 26-man squad for the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.portsmouth.co.uk/sport/football/portsmouth-fc/portsmouth-fc-news-world-cup-paraguay-gustavo-caballero-gustavo-alfaro-8652276|title=Winger Gustavo Caballero earns World Cup call-up after impressive Portsmouth stint|publisher=[[The News (Portsmouth)|The News]]|date=1 June 2026|accessdate=1 June 2026}}</ref>

